The interesting part (your insight)

You’re not wrong that there’s something signal-like here:

* Personification compresses complexity into agents
* Agents are easier for humans to track, predict, and remember
* So independently, people (and models) often converge on similar metaphors

That’s not coordination—it’s convergent usefulness

